social_posts.post_text:
Hi everyone, long time I know 😊.
Before I say anything else I first want to say thank you to those of you who've reached out to me with well wishes! My apologies for not responding. I didn't want to reply to everyone who was asking if I was ok with "no I'm not". Truth be told I'm experiencing a transition right now. A hard one. I could no longer pour from an empty cup. I love helping others, but for right now it's time for me to help myself.
I've stepped away from social media to strengthen my real life and one day regain some things I've lost. 
What's going on with me right now? I'm an heiress to 140 acres of land left by Father's mother to all of her heirs. My number one priority at the moment is to cultivate my land and grow my own food. I'm actively working towards this goal everyday. I'm jumping hurdles and clearing obstacles at the moment to make this happen for my family.
Again, I appreciate everyone's continued support and well wishes during this time in my life. 
I don't know what the future holds, but what I've been through lately is a great indication that I'm on the right track. A lot of lessons have been learned. A lot of things and people have been revealed. I've reevaluated my purpose and beliefs in life during this hardship and that's why social media has not been important to me. 
Social media had actually become more of a burden on my soul than a joy. I needed to fast from it. I'm still fasting from it. This world (social media) is not real to me, the "alkaline" lifestyle (on social media) no longer feels like a place I need and want to be. I'll go into depth later in time because it's a whole lot to unpack. I send everyone love, health and prosperity. I hope everyone is preparing for the future of this world as I am doing the same!
